@bolkerb @RenaudStat is not clear. Like the model here: https://t.co/JkB1aFCo0u is quite a common occurrence in plant breeding and asreml syntax naturally lends better there. Random slope + intercept model is verbose in asreml though so lme4 syntax is nicer there (2/2)

@bolkerb @RenaudStat The difficulty for me with lme4 syntax is that it enforces this hierarchical structure where the upper levels are uncorrelated. So (1+x|g) is fitting random intercept + slope for every level in g and g are uncorrelated. Often in mixed models in plant breeding, hierarchy  (1/2)
